          <td valign="top">

<span class="txth1">HiCurLine : Highlights the current line</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>84/64</b>,
    Downloaded by 3544  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:555">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=96">Charles Campbell</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>This script has a number of maps that intercept various motions and cause the current line to be highlighted.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is a variant of &lt;HiMtchBrkt.vim&gt; (<a href="/tips/tip.php?tip_id=177">vimtip#177</a>).<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\hcli : initiate HiCurLine operation<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\hcls : stop HiCurLine operation<br><br>(see <a href="/tips/tip.php?tip_id=411">vimtip#411</a> to have HiCurLine automatically begin highlighting)<br><br>HiCurLine.vim uses the HL_HiCurLine highlighting group (by default) to specify the highlighting of the current line.&nbsp;&nbsp;One may change the highlighting group HiCurLine uses with the g:HL_HiCurLine variable.&nbsp;&nbsp;By default,<br><br>	let g:HL_HiCurLine= &quot;HL_HiCurLine&quot;<br><br>and &lt;HiCurLine.vim&gt; will specify that group internally.&nbsp;&nbsp;Otherwise, one may change the group used to whatever one wishes:<br><br>	let g:HL_HiCurLine= &quot;Search&quot;<br>	let g:HL_HiCurLine= &quot;Function&quot;<br><br>etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;The default highlighting is: (background is a setting, see :he 'bg')<br><br>	background == dark : blue text on cyan background<br>	background == light: cyan text on blue background<br><br>(alpha/beta version available at <a target="_blank" href="http://mysite.verizon.net/astronaut/vim/index.html#HICURLINE">http://mysite.verizon.net/astronaut/vim/index.html#HICURLINE</A>)<br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>1. Put into your .vim/plugin or<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; _vimfiles\plugin directory (Unix/Windows)<br>2. \hcli (actually &lt;Leader&gt; hcli) will<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; begin the highlighting.<br>3. \hcls will terminate HiCurLine activity, restoring any previous maps, etc. (actually &lt;Leader&gt;hcls)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; (see :he mapleader for more on how to customize the leading characters of mappings)<br><br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

